1
00:00:52,760 --> 00:00:54,760
别擦  孩子
No, son. Never.

2
00:00:55,760 --> 00:00:58,360
血要留在刀刃上
The blood stays on the blade.

3
00:01:01,160 --> 00:01:03,460
总有一天你会明白的
One day you'll understand.

4
00:01:12,560 --> 00:01:14,860
关于往事我只剩一半记忆
Some of it I half remember.

5
00:01:15,460 --> 00:01:17,360
其余的...
And the rest...

6
00:01:18,060 --> 00:01:20,660
其余的从梦里得来
The rest I took from dreams.

7
00:01:24,360 --> 00:01:27,660
圣米歇尔  总领天使在战斗中保佑我们
St. Michael, the archangel, defend us in battle.

8
00:01:27,960 --> 00:01:32,360
是我们的守护神...
Be our protector against the snares...

9
00:01:33,060 --> 00:01:36,160
帮助我们对抗魔鬼的邪恶和陷阱
...and the wickedness of the devil.

10
00:01:36,460 --> 00:01:38,160
好了  孩子  那是谁?
Now, son, who's that?

11
00:01:38,460 --> 00:01:40,160
圣米歇尔  上面是谁?
-St. Michael. -Who is it?

12
00:01:40,360 --> 00:01:42,260
-圣米歇尔  -他的使命?
-St. Michael! -And what did he do?

13
00:01:42,460 --> 00:01:45,160
他把撒旦逐出天堂
He cast Satan out of paradise.

14
00:01:45,760 --> 00:01:47,560
好孩子
Good boy.

15
00:02:57,960 --> 00:03:00,660
主将圣灵的力量注入你们的脊梁...
May God put the steel of the Holy Spirit in your spine...

16
00:03:00,960 --> 00:03:03,660
...将圣母的爱放入你们的心中
...and the love of the Blessed Virgin in your heart.

17
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:33,160
-哥们  -约翰尼
-Hey, boyo! -Johnny.

18
00:03:33,460 --> 00:03:36,260
-哪几方交战?  -本地帮对死兔帮
-What's the battle? - Natives against the Dead Rabbits.

19
00:03:36,560 --> 00:03:40,160
-你是哪边的?  -你说呢?当然是死兔帮
- Which are you? - What do you think? Dead Rabbits.

20
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:22,660
蒙克...
Well, well, Monk.

21
00:04:23,060 --> 00:04:24,960
你是否随我们去?
Are you with us or not?

22
00:04:25,160 --> 00:04:28,260
最后一次了  瓦伦如果开价合理我就去
For the last time, Vallon, I'm with you if the money is right.

23
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:32,160
每条刀痕10元
I'll give you 10 per notch.

24
00:04:32,560 --> 00:04:36,060
-10元?  -我说话算数
-Ten? -You have my word.

25
00:04:40,360 --> 00:04:44,060
-每条刀痕10元?  -新的才算数
-Ten per notch? -Per new notch.

26
00:04:47,860 --> 00:04:49,660
我为你们效力
Then I'm your man.

27
00:06:38,560 --> 00:06:41,260
就这么些人?牧师?  教皇陛下的新人马?
Is this it, Priest? The pope's new army?

28
00:06:41,660 --> 00:06:44,860
几条莽汉和贱民?
A few crusty bitches and a handful of ragtags?

29
00:06:45,160 --> 00:06:48,560
比尔  你说过这是勇者之战
Now, now, Bill, you swore this was a battle between warriors...

30
00:06:48,760 --> 00:06:51,060
...可不是泼妇骂街
...not a bunch of Miss Nancys.

31
00:06:51,360 --> 00:06:54,160
所以我只把战士带来了
So warriors is what I brought.

32
00:06:57,160 --> 00:06:58,460
奥康尔卫士帮
The O'Connell Guard.

33
00:06:58,760 --> 00:07:00,160
搅屎棍帮
The Plug Uglies.

34
00:07:00,360 --> 00:07:02,660
屁帘帮
The Shirt Tails.

35
00:07:07,670 --> 00:07:09,270
齐切斯特帮
The Chichesters.

36
00:07:09,570 --> 00:07:12,270
四十大盗帮
The forty Thieves.

37
00:07:28,570 --> 00:07:31,070
我发出挑战...
On my challenge...

38
00:07:31,370 --> 00:07:36,970
...依据决斗的老规矩
...by the ancient laws of combat, we have met at this chosen ground...

39
00:07:37,270 --> 00:07:39,570
...我们选择在此决斗...
...to settle, for good and all...

40
00:07:39,870 --> 00:07:43,670
...以决定哪方永久持有五点区的控制权
...who holds sway over the Five Points:

41
00:07:44,170 --> 00:07:49,670
决定这块乐土是归于土生土长的地头蛇
Us Natives, born right-wise to this fine land...

42
00:07:50,170 --> 00:07:52,870
...还是沦落于外国蛮子控制之下
...or the foreign hordes defiling it.

43
00:07:57,470 --> 00:08:02,470
依据决斗的老规矩  我接受所谓本地帮的挑战
By the ancient laws of combat, I accept the challenge of the so-called Natives.

44
00:08:02,870 --> 00:08:05,170
你们常陷我们于水火之中
You plague our people at every turn.

45
00:08:05,370 --> 00:08:08,170
从今天起  你们无法再欺凌我们
But from this day out, you shall plague us no more.

46
00:08:08,470 --> 00:08:12,070
我们要让大家知道  想把我们推出这片土地的手...
For let it be known that the hand that tries to strike us from this land...

47
00:08:12,470 --> 00:08:14,070
...理应一刀砍去
...shall be swiftly cut down.

48
00:08:16,270 --> 00:08:19,570
让基督教徒藉主的指引
Then may the Christian Lord guide my hand...

49
00:08:19,970 --> 00:08:22,070
...对抗你们这帮天主教徒
...against your Roman popery!

50
00:08:22,370 --> 00:08:25,070
准备迎纳真正的主吧
Prepare to receive the true Lord!

51
00:10:28,170 --> 00:10:29,970
牧师
Priest!

52
00:11:18,170 --> 00:11:20,470
看着我
Look to me.

53
00:11:21,870 --> 00:11:24,770
谁倒在我的刀下?
Who is this under my knife?

54
00:11:32,970 --> 00:11:35,370
爸爸  起来  起来
Father, get up. Get up!

55
00:11:35,670 --> 00:11:39,070
你在哪?  你在哪?
Where are you? Where are you?

56
00:11:40,570 --> 00:11:42,070
我的孩子
Oh, my son.

57
00:11:45,370 --> 00:11:48,970
别把脸转过去
Don't never look away.

58
00:11:56,270 --> 00:11:58,870
很快就结束了  牧师
Soon be over, Priest.

59
00:12:00,870 --> 00:12:02,770
了结我吧
Finish it.

60
00:12:20,970 --> 00:12:23,770
了结我吧
You may need this across the river.

61
00:12:32,870 --> 00:12:36,170
可以割下鼻子耳朵作为今天的战利品
Ears and noses will be the trophies of the day.

62
00:12:37,070 --> 00:12:40,670
但此人谁也不许碰
But no hand shall touch him!

63
00:12:42,970 --> 00:12:45,770
谁也不许碰他
No hand shall touch him!

64
00:12:47,870 --> 00:12:50,370
他死得...
He'll cross over whole...

65
00:12:51,470 --> 00:12:53,070
...有尊严
...in honor.

66
00:12:53,370 --> 00:12:55,970
先让我拿走他欠我的钱
Not before I get what's owed.

67
00:13:02,770 --> 00:13:04,670
别动
No!

68
00:13:05,770 --> 00:13:10,070
很公平  虽然不是很得体  但很公平
It's fair. A touch indelicate, but fair.

69
00:13:14,870 --> 00:13:16,770
我深表同情
My sympathies.

70
00:13:17,770 --> 00:13:19,370
怎么处理这小子?
What will we do with the boy?

71
00:13:19,880 --> 00:13:21,980
看着我
Look at me.

72
00:13:27,780 --> 00:13:29,280
把他交给警察
Give him to the law.

73
00:13:29,580 --> 00:13:32,180
他能受到好的教育
See he gets a good education.

74
00:13:32,980 --> 00:13:35,780
小子  和你爸爸道别吧
Okay, boy, say goodbye to your father.

75
00:13:42,980 --> 00:13:45,080
-抓住他  -抓住他
-Get him! -Get him!

76
00:13:46,180 --> 00:13:47,580
别让他跑了
Don't let him get away.

77
00:13:47,780 --> 00:13:50,080
快点  来这
Hurry, come in here!

78
00:13:52,380 --> 00:13:53,980
他跑到下面去了
He's going downstairs.

79
00:14:10,480 --> 00:14:11,680
过来  小子
Come here, boy.

80
00:14:11,880 --> 00:14:14,680
-你跑不了了  小子  -他在这  抓住他
-You're going to Hellgate, son. -There he is. Get him.

81
00:14:14,880 --> 00:14:17,780
牧师瓦伦死的光荣
- Priest Vallon died a noble death... - Let go of me!

82
00:14:18,180 --> 00:14:23,380
他的死兔帮也寿终正寝了
...but his Dead Rabbits is done and outlawed!

83
00:14:25,380 --> 00:14:30,180
从今往后谁也不许提到这些名字
Let no one even speak their name from this time on.

84
00:15:15,080 --> 00:15:20,380
在这个地方  在这个地方
In this place, you have grown from a boy into a man.

85
00:15:22,380 --> 00:15:25,980
要摒弃你过去种种罪孽  无仁  无义
Put to death the earthly things in you: Immorality, impurity...

86
00:15:26,280 --> 00:15:28,880
冲动  报复欲
...passion, vengeance.

87
00:15:29,080 --> 00:15:32,280
主已经宽恕了你
The Lord has forgiven you.

88
00:15:32,580 --> 00:15:35,780
你也必须宽恕自己
You also must forgive.

89
00:15:36,680 --> 00:15:39,280
你要前往一个因暴力争斗而四分五裂的地区(罪人之路艰难困苦)
You go forth to a country torn apart by civil strife.

90
00:15:41,780 --> 00:15:43,680
谢谢您  牧师
Thank you, Reverend.

91
00:15:46,780 --> 00:15:49,480
为未竟之事业尽一份力
Lend your hand to the work that yet remains...

92
00:15:49,780 --> 00:15:51,880
...希望纷争可以结束...
...that this war may end...

93
00:15:52,080 --> 00:15:55,380
...给人类带来巨大灾难的奴隶制度...
...and the plague of slavery that brought this conflagration...

94
00:15:55,680 --> 00:16:00,880
...在地球上消失无踪
...down upon us vanish forever from the earth.

95
00:16:31,680 --> 00:16:33,480
南北战争的第二年
In the second year of the Civil War...

96
00:16:33,780 --> 00:16:36,280
...正是爱尔兰人上街游行的时候...
...when the Irish Brigade marched in the streets...

97
00:16:36,480 --> 00:16:39,380
...纽约是个族裔众多...
...New York was a city full of tribes...

98
00:16:39,780 --> 00:16:42,980
...军官林立  贫富纷杂的都市
...war chiefs, rich and poor.

99
00:16:43,280 --> 00:16:46,880
-打倒林肯  -林肯想把所有白人变成奴隶
-Down with Lincoln! - Lincoln will make all white men slaves.

100
00:16:47,480 --> 00:16:48,980
这真算不上是一个城市
It wasn 't a city really.

101
00:16:50,780 --> 00:16:54,480
更象是一个大熔炉  也许某天能融会锻造出一个城市来
It was more a furnace where a city someday might be forged.

102
00:16:54,880 --> 00:16:56,380
就是这样  小伙子们
That's the spirit, boys.

103
00:16:56,680 --> 00:17:00,880
快为你们的黑鬼朋友送命去吧  打倒废奴者
- Go off and die for your blackie friends. - Down with the abolitionists!

104
00:17:01,180 --> 00:17:04,280
我们得找机会选出一个更强有力的人物来对抗林肯
We shoule run a better man against Lincoln when we had the chance.

105
00:17:04,480 --> 00:17:06,280
纽约要脱离联邦
New York should secede from the Union!

106
00:17:06,580 --> 00:17:09,180
他想尽力表明我们和黑鬼们没区别?
They trying to say we're no different than niggers?

107
00:17:09,480 --> 00:17:12,280
当然有区别  -晚上好  兄弟  -上帝拯救联邦
You ain't. Good evening, brother.

108
00:17:12,880 --> 00:17:14,680
-上帝拯救联邦  这就是联邦
-Praise the Union. - The Union forever!

109
00:17:14,880 --> 00:17:17,680
滚回非洲去  黑鬼
Go back to Africa, nigger!

110
00:17:18,280 --> 00:17:21,080
滚回非洲去  -放开他  我们自由了
-Go back to Africa! -Leave him alone. We're free.

111
00:17:21,380 --> 00:17:24,380
最引起公愤的是新征兵法
The angriest talk was of the new Conscription Act...

112
00:17:24,580 --> 00:17:26,380
联邦史上头号征兵法
...the first draft in Union history.

113
00:17:39,480 --> 00:17:43,080
参军吧  小伙子  一天三餐  待遇优厚
Join the Army, lads. Three square meals a day and good pay in your pocket.

114
00:17:43,380 --> 00:17:46,680
爱尔兰人来的时候  这个城市一片狂热
When the Irish came, the city was in a fever.

115
00:17:46,980 --> 00:17:51,280
自本土发生大饥荒以来  爱尔兰人乘船如潮水般涌至
Since the time of the great famine, they'd come streaming off the boats.

116
00:17:51,680 --> 00:17:53,380
他们受到了热烈的欢迎
And they got a right warm welcome.

117
00:17:53,680 --> 00:17:56,880
-滚回家去  爱尔兰傻瓜  -记住了  死鬼爱尔兰人
-Go back to Ireland, you dumb micks! -Remember that, you Irish gyps!

118
00:17:57,280 --> 00:17:59,080
滚回船上去
Get back on the boat, Paddy!

119
00:17:59,880 --> 00:18:02,880
我来自船程仅两小时的地狱门
I only came two hours downriver from Hellgate.

120
00:18:03,180 --> 00:18:05,480
可别人把我当成外来移民
But they all took me for an immigrant.

121
00:18:05,780 --> 00:18:08,680
为什么不呢?  纽约本地就有上千种口音
Why not? There were a thousand different accents in New York.

122
00:18:08,980 --> 00:18:13,480
我和移民也没不同
And to the Natives, you see, we was all the same.

123
00:18:18,880 --> 00:18:22,180
欢迎来到美国  孩子  漫长艰巨的旅途结束了
Welcome to America, son. Your long, arduous journey is over.

124
00:18:22,580 --> 00:18:24,880
-滚回你的国家去  -投坦慕尼一票
-Go back to your own country! -Vote Tammany!

125
00:18:32,880 --> 00:18:36,780
纽约对威廉.特威德既爱且恨
New York loved William Tweed and hated him.

126
00:18:37,080 --> 00:18:41,280
我们这些想作小偷的人  忍不住对他肃然起敬
And those of us trying to be thieves, well, we couldn 't help but admire him.

127
00:18:41,780 --> 00:18:44,980
卡丁先生  先生们  多谢光临  非常荣幸
Mr. Cutting, gentlemen, thank you for coming. It's an honor.

128
00:18:45,180 --> 00:18:46,980
特威德先生
Mr. Tweed.

129
00:18:49,180 --> 00:18:51,380
先生  请别这样
Sir, please. Excuse me.

130
00:18:51,780 --> 00:18:53,980
-你吓着它们了  -那怎么了?
-I think you're frightening them. -So?

131
00:18:54,180 --> 00:18:57,780
别介意  他以前是爱尔兰人
Don't mind him. He used to be an Irishman.

132
00:18:59,380 --> 00:19:01,080
五点区
Ah, the Five Points.

133
00:19:01,480 --> 00:19:06,280
杀手巷  碎砖大楼  地狱门
Murderers' Alley. Brickbat Mansion. The Gates of Hell.

134
00:19:06,680 --> 00:19:12,280
就是这个简陋的地方  看看这个可怜的孩子的脸
Here in this vile place. Look upon the face of this poor child.

135
00:19:12,680 --> 00:19:15,180
她居住的环境肮脏潦倒...
She lives in squalor...

136
00:19:15,580 --> 00:19:19,780
...就在我后面这个破败凄凉的狗窝里
...in this godforsaken den of vice and misery behind me.

137
00:19:20,380 --> 00:19:22,680
改良派年年来
Every year the reformers came.

138
00:19:22,980 --> 00:19:24,580
五点区却越来越糟...
Every year the Points got worse...

139
00:19:26,980 --> 00:19:28,680
...仿佛它天生不爱干净(五点区教会)
...as if it liked being dirty.

140
00:19:29,680 --> 00:19:32,880
-我要去哪里?  -走!  牧师让你离开这里
-Where am I going to go? - The Reverend wants you out of here.

141
00:19:33,190 --> 00:19:35,390
你不能这么作
You can't do this!

142
00:19:40,890 --> 00:19:44,190
你这条臭蛆
...to which these miserable creatures have fallen.

143
00:19:47,390 --> 00:19:50,890
比尔也许你知道   我每天都到码头去
You may or may not know, Bill, that every day I go to the waterfront...

144
00:19:51,090 --> 00:19:53,690
...为刚到埠的爱尔兰人奉上热汤
...with hot soup for the Irish as they come ashore.

145
00:19:53,990 --> 00:19:55,890
这是打好政治基础的一部分
It's part of building a political base.

146
00:19:56,190 --> 00:19:58,990
我在那留意到你了你应该也见到我了
I've noticed you there. You may have noticed me.

147
00:19:59,390 --> 00:20:02,490
确实如此  你肆意羞辱
Indeed I have. Throwing torrents of pavers and withering abuse...

148
00:20:02,790 --> 00:20:06,190
对每个下船的人都  如果只有我有枪
...on everyone stepping off those boats. - Lf only I had the guns...

149
00:20:06,590 --> 00:20:11,190
...那帮家伙一踏上美国土地我就宰了他们
...I'd shoot each and every one of them before they set foot on American soil.

150
00:20:36,790 --> 00:20:39,190
墨贝理街...
Mulberry Street...

151
00:20:39,990 --> 00:20:41,690
...沃什区
...and Worth.

152
00:20:41,990 --> 00:20:46,490
十字区橘子区
Cross and Orange and Little Water.

153
00:20:46,890 --> 00:20:49,690
五点的每个区都是一根手指
Each of the Five Points is a finger.

154
00:20:49,890 --> 00:20:54,090
我一握紧手  它就变成了拳头
When I close my hand, it becomes a fist.

155
00:20:54,490 --> 00:20:58,390
只要我愿意  我就把拳头对着你
And any time that I wish, I can turn it against you.

156
00:20:58,690 --> 00:21:00,890
我明白  但我们谈的是两回事
I know, but we're talking about different things.

157
00:21:01,190 --> 00:21:04,490
我谈的是公民义务  我们对大众应负的责任
I'm talking about civic duty, responsibilities we owe to the people.

158
00:21:04,690 --> 00:21:07,490
学校、医院、下水道、公用设施
Schools and hospitals, sewers and utilities.

159
00:21:07,890 --> 00:21:10,090
道路建设、修整及清洁
Street construction, repairs and sweeping.

160
00:21:10,390 --> 00:21:12,490
营业执照  酒吧执照
Business licenses, saloon licenses...

161
00:21:33,790 --> 00:21:38,090
圣米歇尔  总领天使  在作战中保佑我们
St. Michael, the archangel, defend us in battle.

162
00:21:38,490 --> 00:21:42,090
是我们的守护神帮助我们对抗魔鬼
Be our protector against the snares and the wickedness of the devil.

163
00:21:42,490 --> 00:21:44,990
街车  轮渡  垃圾处理
Street cars, ferries, rubbish disposal.

164
00:21:45,290 --> 00:21:47,990
以及这座城市创造财富的能力  比尔
There's a power of money to be made in this city, Bill.

165
00:21:48,290 --> 00:21:52,190
有你的帮助  应该让人们明白
With your help, the people must be made to understand...

166
00:21:52,490 --> 00:21:56,490
...这一切必须在我称之为'坦慕尼大家庭'之中
...that all these things are best kept within the Tammany family...

167
00:21:56,790 --> 00:21:58,890
...才能运作的最好
...which is why I'm proposing an alliance...

168
00:21:59,190 --> 00:22:01,490
...所以我才找你商谈我们两大团体之间的结盟
...between our two great organizations.

169
00:22:01,790 --> 00:22:05,890
-你说的都是力气活  -没错  加强力量正是我们的精神
-You're talking about muscle work. - That too. Muscle to match our spirit.

170
00:22:06,290 --> 00:22:08,090
你手里有警察  可以让他们去做
You own the crushers. Get them to do it.

171
00:22:08,290 --> 00:22:10,090
警察?  不行!
The police? Oh, no. Jesus, no!

172
00:22:10,390 --> 00:22:14,090
法律的形象必须得维护...
The appearance of the law must be upheld...

173
00:22:14,390 --> 00:22:16,890
...法将不法的时候更得维护
...especially while it's being broken.

174
00:22:28,390 --> 00:22:31,790
赐予我力量以完成我的使命
Give me the strength for what I must do.

175
00:22:34,790 --> 00:22:36,590
你是谁?
Who are you?

176
00:22:39,190 --> 00:22:40,990
-别动
-Hey! -No!

177
00:22:41,290 --> 00:22:44,390
我问你  你是谁?  你在这里做什么?
I said, who are you? What are you doing here?

178
00:22:51,990 --> 00:22:54,790
我只是喜欢来这里  这这样
I just like it down here is all.

179
00:22:55,690 --> 00:22:58,090
搜搜他的身  吉米
See what's in his pockets, Jimmy.

180
00:22:58,390 --> 00:23:01,790
-听着  伙计们  我真的不想打架  -不想打架?
-Look, boys, I really don't want a fight. -Don't want a fight?

181
00:23:01,990 --> 00:23:05,090
别担心  小子  不会打架的
Don't worry, son, ain't gonna be much a fight.

182
00:23:12,490 --> 00:23:14,290
别杀我
Don't kill me.

183
00:23:22,390 --> 00:23:24,290
你从哪找到这东西的?
Where'd you get that?

184
00:23:24,590 --> 00:23:26,890
我说了不想打架的
I told you I didn't want a fight!

185
00:23:27,190 --> 00:23:29,790
为什么?  看你身手多好啊
Why not? Look how good you done.

186
00:23:37,290 --> 00:23:41,790
-你是牧师的儿子吗?  -你离我远点  明白吗?
-You're the Priest's son, aren't you? -You, get away from me, understand?

187
00:23:42,190 --> 00:23:46,690
你不记得我了?  我就是那个想救你命的人
You don't remember me, do you? I's the one tried to help you.

188
00:23:48,690 --> 00:23:51,490
-什么?  -我就是那个想救你命的人...
-What? -I's the one tried to help you...

189
00:23:51,790 --> 00:23:53,990
...在本地帮抓你的时候
...when the Natives took you.

190
00:23:57,690 --> 00:24:02,490
-是你吗?  -是的  我以为你被杀了
-Oh, that was you? -Yeah. I thought you was killed.

191
00:24:05,390 --> 00:24:07,290
他们只是把我关起来了
They just locked me up, you know that?

192
00:24:07,590 --> 00:24:09,490
这么久?
This long?

193
00:24:09,690 --> 00:24:14,390
可我总是想方设法逃跑  他们就把我多关了些日子
Well, I kept trying to escape, you know. They add on time for that.

194
00:24:15,690 --> 00:24:18,190
你回来做什么?
So, what are you doing back here?

195
00:24:18,890 --> 00:24:20,890
我想念这个地方
I guess I missed the place.

196
00:24:27,890 --> 00:24:29,490
鲍瑞街的混小子
Bowery Boys.

197
00:24:41,990 --> 00:24:43,390
给我回来
Get back here!

198
00:24:43,590 --> 00:24:46,290
五点区  天堂广场
The Five Points, Paradise Square.

199
00:24:46,590 --> 00:24:49,490
到了晚上街道总是生机勃勃
The streets here are always lively of an evening.

200
00:24:50,690 --> 00:24:52,290
现在都有些什么帮派?
Who are the gangs around now?

201
00:24:52,590 --> 00:24:54,490
有'黎明小子'和'沼泽探子'
The Daybreak Boys and the Swamp Angels.

202
00:24:54,690 --> 00:24:56,790
他们在河上以抢劫船只谋生
They work the river, looting ships.

203
00:24:57,090 --> 00:24:59,690
上海水手青蛙帮在血天使区一带活动
The frog Hollows shanghai sailors by the Bloody Angle.

204
00:24:59,890 --> 00:25:03,290
'屁帘帮'一度强盛  现在成为'花花公子帮'一部分
The Shirt Tails was rough, but they've become a bunch of dandies...

205
00:25:03,490 --> 00:25:06,290
...在杀手街盘踞  穿得象中国人
...Iolling around Murderers' Alley, looking like Chinamen.

206
00:25:06,790 --> 00:25:09,390
地狱猫麦姬-自己开了个酒吧
Hell-Cat Maggie, she tried to open her own grog shop.

207
00:25:09,590 --> 00:25:12,190
可惜酒全被她自己喝完了  结果被人赶到大街上
She drunk her own liquor and got throwed on the street.

208
00:25:12,390 --> 00:25:14,890
-真漂亮  -现从事各种非法勾当
-Beautiful. -Now she's on the lay for anything.

209
00:25:15,090 --> 00:25:17,590
还有搅屎棍帮  不知道从哪个国家的角落来的
The Plug Uglies are from deep in the old country.

210
00:25:17,790 --> 00:25:19,990
有自己的语言
Got their own language no one understands.

211
00:25:20,190 --> 00:25:23,490
他们喜欢找警察的茬  还有破烂街的'夜行人帮'
They love to fight the cops. The Night Walkers of Ragpicker's Row.

212
00:25:24,090 --> 00:25:26,690
喜欢鬼鬼祟祟跟在人后面把人掐死
They work on their backs and kill with their hands.

213
00:25:26,890 --> 00:25:30,490
他们如此卑鄙  只有搅屎棍帮愿意与他们搭腔  可天知道他们在说什么?
They're so scurvy only the Plug Uglies talk to them. But who understands them?

214
00:25:30,990 --> 00:25:33,290
还有'屠场屠夫'和'百老汇舞者'
The Slaughter Housers and the Broadway Twisters.

215
00:25:33,590 --> 00:25:36,590
都是一群赌棍  以及四十小盗
They're a fine bunch of bingo boys. And the Little forty Thieves.

216
00:25:36,890 --> 00:25:38,190
我曾和他们厮混过一段...
I used to run with them...

217
00:25:38,490 --> 00:25:41,290
...直到他们被本德里克收并
...till they got took over by Bendrick the Cockroach.

218
00:25:41,490 --> 00:25:42,990
本德里克是个混蛋兼小人
Bendrick carries a germ.

219
00:25:43,190 --> 00:25:45,990
他订了个规矩  谁敢离开帮派就给谁放血
If you try to leave the gang, he hacks up blood on you.

220
00:25:46,300 --> 00:25:49,600
可他们只会在街头巷尾诅咒英国
The lime-juicers are nothing but a bunch of rapacious grab-ups.

221
00:25:50,500 --> 00:25:52,700
'真蓝美国人'自称帮派...
The True Blue Americans say they're a gang...

222
00:25:53,000 --> 00:25:55,600
...可他们只会在街头巷尾诅咒英国
...but all they do is stand on corners damning England.

223
00:25:55,900 --> 00:25:59,000
如果你相信英国佬任何一句话  你就是个傻瓜
If you believe one word the British say, you're a fool.

224
00:25:59,300 --> 00:26:02,500
有没有人接手'死兔帮'?
Do any of them got the sand of the Dead Rabbits?

225
00:26:06,300 --> 00:26:08,300
你不能提这个名字
You don't say that name.

226
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:13,100
这个名字已经死去  和你的...  这些都被取缔了
That name died with your... They been outlawed.

227
00:26:13,800 --> 00:26:15,700
我被关押期间  中国佬告诉我...
In the blockhouse, the Chinks told me...

228
00:26:15,900 --> 00:26:20,100
...本地帮每年都在庆祝胜利  是不是真的?
...that the Natives celebrate their victory every year. Is that true?

229
00:26:20,800 --> 00:26:23,200
确实如此  算是件大事
Aye, that they do. It's quite the affair.

230
00:26:23,500 --> 00:26:26,200
屠夫亲自邀请过你  你不去
The Butcher himself's got to invite you, or you don't go.

231
00:26:37,000 --> 00:26:39,800
你怎么走的路  约翰尼
Look where you're going, Johnny.

232
00:26:42,600 --> 00:26:45,400
你看起来象只呆头鹅
You look stunned and poorly, sir.

233
00:26:49,800 --> 00:26:52,900
好一对演说家
Quite a pair of conversationists, aren't you?

234
00:26:55,200 --> 00:26:58,600
不对  我们都是思想家
Maybe not, but we're deep thinkers.

235
00:27:02,200 --> 00:27:08,100
先生们  我留你们继续享受上帝的恩惠和关怀
Well, gentlemen, I leave you in the grace and favor of the Lord.

236
00:27:15,400 --> 00:27:17,900
珍妮  最棒的妙手空空
Jenny, the finest bludget in all the Points.

237
00:27:18,200 --> 00:27:20,700
我觉得她象个美艳的算命小姐
She is a prim-looking stargazer.

238
00:27:23,500 --> 00:27:25,800
你最好检查一下口袋...
But I'd check my pockets if I was you...

239
00:27:26,000 --> 00:27:29,200
...我相信她把你的表偷走了
...because I do believe she lifted your timepiece.

240
00:27:33,200 --> 00:27:35,600
我让她拿的
Well, I let her take it.

241
00:27:35,900 --> 00:27:38,500
我的东西随便让她拿
I let her take things all the time.

242
00:27:39,100 --> 00:27:41,500
-是吗?  -是的
-Is that right? -Yeah.

243
00:27:46,200 --> 00:27:48,500
我们总是希望在五点区能来点火灾
We always liked a good fire in the Points.

244
00:27:49,800 --> 00:27:55,300
通常可以顺手牵羊  如果警察来了  还有好戏可看
You could pick up a little swag. And if the cops came, you really got a show.

245
00:27:55,700 --> 00:27:59,000
由市属警察迎战都会警察
The Municipal Police fought the Metropolitan Police.

246
00:27:59,300 --> 00:28:01,900
都会警察则迎战街头黑帮
The Metropolitan Police, they fought the street gangs.

247
00:28:02,300 --> 00:28:04,600
快点  伙计们  要赶在'黑杰克'之前
Hurry up, men, before the Black Joke get there!

248
00:28:04,800 --> 00:28:08,400
还有37个业余消防队  也彼此缠斗不休
There were 37 amateur fire brigades, and they all fought each other.

249
00:28:08,800 --> 00:28:14,400
黑杰克正在路上  特威德  他们会把你们打惨的
The Black Joke are on their way, Tweed, and they'll beat the shite out of you.

250
00:28:17,000 --> 00:28:22,700
好了  小伙子们
Okay, boys, get the hose out!

251
00:28:28,100 --> 00:28:30,500
黑杰克来了
It's the Black Joke!

252
00:28:30,800 --> 00:28:33,100
去挡住他们  小伙子们
Go get them, boys!

253
00:28:34,000 --> 00:28:36,300
给他们点颜色瞧瞧
Give those Bowery Boys hell!

254
00:28:36,600 --> 00:28:40,000
快点  别被人全拿走了  滚出去  你们这帮浑蛋
-Quick, before there's nothing left. -Go back to the Bowery, you bums!

255
00:28:40,300 --> 00:28:43,000
快制止他们  天啊他们把东西全拿跑了
Stop them. For God's sake, they're taking everything!

256
00:28:43,300 --> 00:28:45,900
以后再遇到麻烦夫人  先找坦慕尼
In your next time of trouble, call on Tammany first.

257
00:28:46,300 --> 00:28:49,500
可还为时未晚  你们还可以挽救我的房子
But it's not too late. You can still save my house.

258
00:28:50,200 --> 00:28:51,800
走吧
Let's go.

259
00:28:52,700 --> 00:28:55,500
你说你饿了
I thought you said you was hungry.

260
00:28:59,000 --> 00:29:02,400
尽可能多拿些!  快走吧!
Grab what you can, Johnny. Let's get out of here.

261
00:29:03,300 --> 00:29:06,000
需要我告诉你这座房子会烧会灰吗?
May I point out that this building is burning to ashes?

262
00:29:06,300 --> 00:29:10,400
需要我告诉你这里是属于阿梅里克斯消防队管辖的区域
May I point out this area is the province of my own Americus fire Brigade...

263
00:29:10,800 --> 00:29:14,100
你们的范围仅限于鲍瑞吗?
...and that you lot belong only in the Bowery?

264
00:29:15,500 --> 00:29:18,400
需要我告诉你你们已经处于下风  劣势
May I point out that you're outmanned, outmaneuvered...

265
00:29:18,600 --> 00:29:20,700
并且快要被打败了吗?
...and, in a moment, outfought?

266
00:29:20,900 --> 00:29:22,700
是吗?
Am I?

267
00:29:28,600 --> 00:29:31,600
黑杰克在这里让他们别挡道
There's the Black Joke! Let's take them on the cobbles.

268
00:29:31,900 --> 00:29:36,100
去饱揍他们一顿
Go spill some claret, boys. Go on, Shorty, have a nice muss.

269
00:29:36,500 --> 00:29:39,000
为屠夫比尔开道
Clear the way for Bill the Butcher.

270
00:29:39,300 --> 00:29:41,300
好吧  小伙子们  动手吧
Okay, boys, to work.

271
00:29:42,600 --> 00:29:46,200
到底要干什么?  屋里值钱的东西差不多全烧光了
What's the point? The fire's near burned anything of value inside.

272
00:29:46,500 --> 00:29:49,600
小伙子们  别管这幢了  去旁边那幢
Boys, forget that one. Next building over.

273
00:29:50,000 --> 00:29:52,700
不能让火蔓延开  那房子的东西随便拿
Mustn't let it spread. Take what you want from that one.

274
00:29:53,000 --> 00:29:53,900
你们干什么?
What are you doing?

275
00:29:54,100 --> 00:29:56,800
这房子没问题啊  这是我的房子
There's nothing wrong with this one. This is my house.

276
00:30:00,800 --> 00:30:02,200
-约翰尼  -救命
-Johnny! -Help!

277
00:30:02,400 --> 00:30:04,800
-约翰尼  -救命
- Johnny! -Help!

278
00:30:06,300 --> 00:30:09,000
救命  救命
Help! Help!

279
00:30:13,100 --> 00:30:14,800
救命
Help!

280
00:30:18,900 --> 00:30:21,000
快走  快走  约翰尼  起来
Come on. Come on, Johnny, get up.

281
00:30:21,500 --> 00:30:23,300
别拿了
Leave that!

282
00:30:30,700 --> 00:30:32,000
你们俩快走开
You two, out of the way!

283
00:30:49,500 --> 00:30:51,600
他叫阿姆斯特丹
His name's Amsterdam.

284
00:30:54,200 --> 00:30:57,100
货色如何?  还行
- How's the beak? - Ain't so bad.

285
00:30:57,400 --> 00:31:01,300
你  有东西就交出来  要不就出去
You. You got anything, you give it up or you get out.

286
00:31:12,700 --> 00:31:14,500
就这些?
Is that it?

287
00:31:15,000 --> 00:31:16,900
就这些
That's it.

288
00:31:18,400 --> 00:31:21,600
好了  跟你说规矩  交来这的所有东西  由我们变卖
Right. Here's the rake. Everything comes here. We fence it.

289
00:31:21,900 --> 00:31:25,200
约翰尼把贡金交给本地帮  然后我们分配所得
Johnny takes our tribute to the Natives, and we chop up the winnings...

290
00:31:25,600 --> 00:31:28,900
根据每个人在帮中的地位
...each to his equal portion, amongst the gang.

291
00:31:29,200 --> 00:31:32,500
这规矩你满意吗?地狱门?
Does that meet with your approval, Hellgate?

292
00:31:32,900 --> 00:31:34,500
我满意吗?
My approval?

293
00:31:34,700 --> 00:31:37,500
什么意思?杰克你不会自己动脑子吗?
What's the matter, Jack Sprat? Can't think for yourself?

294
00:31:39,200 --> 00:31:42,100
-我撕烂你的喉咙  -来呀
-I'll slit your fucking throat! -Hey, come on!

295
00:31:47,100 --> 00:31:51,000
你们分赃之前该先和我算算帐
You boys will settle with me before settling with each other.

296
00:31:54,600 --> 00:31:57,200
我来要我的份子钱
I come for my due and proper.

297
00:32:16,310 --> 00:32:18,310
收获不小啊
Well, this ain't a bad haul.

298
00:32:18,910 --> 00:32:22,310
别人问我这个关于国家前景我怎么说吗?
When folks start in to saying to where the country is going to hell...

299
00:32:22,610 --> 00:32:29,110
...我总是告诉他们  '到五点区去观摩那些棒小伙多么辛勤工作就知道了...
...I always tell them, "You just look at all the hard work..our fine young lads is doing down in the Five Points."

300
00:32:29,310 --> 00:32:33,210
这东西送穆拉尼夫人正合适
Oh, yeah. Now this is just the thing for Mrs. Mulraney.

301
00:32:33,610 --> 00:32:38,310
这东西送穆拉尼夫人正合适给我们留点东西孝敬屠夫比尔
All right there, Happy Jack, leave us something...to quarter to Bill the Butcher, eh?

302
00:32:38,610 --> 00:32:40,110
行吗?
Would you?

303
00:32:51,710 --> 00:32:54,210
这音乐我不喜欢
Not my favorite tune.

304
00:33:01,510 --> 00:33:03,610
谢了  小伙子们
Thank you, boys.

305
00:33:04,310 --> 00:33:07,210
你们没事了
You keep out of trouble now.

306
00:33:25,410 --> 00:33:29,310
每年本地帮一次次地庆祝我父亲的死...
Every year the Natives celebrated the killing of my father all over again...

307
00:33:31,110 --> 00:33:36,010
...地点就在莫特街中国麻将馆
...at Sparrow's Chinese Pagoda in Mott Street.

308
00:33:36,410 --> 00:33:40,010
中国人比我们还恨本地帮
The Chinks hated the Natives worse than we did.

309
00:33:42,910 --> 00:33:47,010
当鼓声响起屠夫会喝下一杯火酒
The drum rolls, and the Butcher drinks a glass of fire.

310
00:33:51,410 --> 00:33:53,710
要杀死一位国王
When you kill a king...

311
00:33:54,310 --> 00:33:57,210
2分钟你不该在黑暗中狙杀他
...you don 't stab him in the dark.

312
00:33:58,710 --> 00:34:03,810
而要在众目睽睽之下杀了他
You kill him where the whole court can watch him die.

313
00:34:07,810 --> 00:34:10,310
有火吗?
Hey, you got any timber?

314
00:35:00,410 --> 00:35:04,110
-麦琪  左耳还是右耳?  -快给我们酒喝 你这白痴
-Hey, Maggie. Right ear or left ear? -Give us a drink, you idiot.

315
00:35:04,410 --> 00:35:06,010
自己动手吧
Help yourself.

316
00:35:06,210 --> 00:35:08,010
-最后押注!  -为健康干杯
-Final bets! -To health.

317
00:35:08,210 --> 00:35:11,210
快下注吧  最后2分钟
Place your bets. Betting closes in two minutes.

318
00:35:11,410 --> 00:35:12,710
快下注吧
Place your bets.

319
00:35:12,910 --> 00:35:16,910
先生们  比赛要开始了
Gentlemen, the match is due to commence.

320
00:35:17,310 --> 00:35:20,710
数目是三分钟内吃掉25只老鼠
The count to beat is 25 rodents in three minutes.

321
00:35:21,010 --> 00:35:23,210
鼠狗大战
Towser against the vermin.

322
00:35:23,410 --> 00:35:25,110
-大家满意吗?  -50
-Are the enumerators satisfied? -Fifty!

323
00:35:25,310 --> 00:35:27,410
-好的  -放出来吧
-Yes! -Let them go!

324
00:35:41,310 --> 00:35:44,310
-你要干什么  小伙子?  -我来给比尔进贡
-Where you going, boy? -I'm here to pay tribute to Bill.

325
00:35:44,610 --> 00:35:46,910
是吗?  把钱给我  我交给他
Are you now? Give it to me. I'll give it to him.

326
00:35:47,210 --> 00:35:49,910
不用了  多谢  还是我自己来吧
No, thanks. I'll give it to him myself.

327
00:35:51,610 --> 00:35:54,010
你是想留着你的牙齿还是钱?
What do you want to keep, the money or your teeth?

328
00:35:54,310 --> 00:35:55,910
约翰
John.

329
00:35:56,910 --> 00:35:58,410
欢迎
Welcome.

330
00:36:06,410 --> 00:36:08,910
我和我的朋友的  先生
From me and me lads, sir.

331
00:36:15,710 --> 00:36:18,810
你的朋友?  他是哪来的?
Mate of yours? Where's he from?

332
00:36:19,610 --> 00:36:21,810
他不是本地人  先生
Oh, he's not from here, sir.

333
00:36:24,510 --> 00:36:26,210
你
You.

334
00:36:43,610 --> 00:36:45,710
别再走近了
That's close enough.

335
00:36:56,910 --> 00:37:01,310
你朋友没有看着我的眼睛  这可不是很有礼貌的行为
Your friend can't look me in the eye. That's not an admirable characteristic.

336
00:37:01,610 --> 00:37:05,410
没人能看着你的眼睛  比尔  尤其是你玩牌的时候
No one can look you in the eye, Bill. Not when you're playing cards.

337
00:37:24,110 --> 00:37:27,710
这是惠斯特  绅士的游戏  下注该有个绅士的样子
This is whist. It's a gentleman's game. Make a gentleman's bet.

338
00:37:28,210 --> 00:37:32,310
-我下得够大了  比尔  -不够大
-I'm betting large, Bill. -That ain't large.

339
00:37:40,910 --> 00:37:44,010
拜托别再嚷嚷了  哈威
Please, don't make that noise again, Harvey.

340
00:37:46,510 --> 00:37:49,810
我喜欢对财富极度渴望的人
I like a man who's willing to burn for his swag.

341
00:37:53,310 --> 00:37:55,910
你水性好吗?  走近点
How do you fare on water? Come closer.

342
00:37:56,110 --> 00:37:59,310
近点  约翰  我不会咬人的 再近点
Close, John. I ain't gonna bite. Close.

343
00:38:02,810 --> 00:38:06,710
有一艘葡萄牙船停靠在港口  有三个星期的检疫期
There's a Portuguese ship lying low in the harbor, quarantined three weeks.

344
00:38:07,010 --> 00:38:09,010
趁黎明小子洗劫前下手
Get there before the Daybreak Boys strip her...

345
00:38:09,310 --> 00:38:10,910
2分钟可能我们还得仔细商量一下
...maybe you and me will talk more.

346
00:38:11,210 --> 00:38:13,610
-没问题  先生  -好样的
-Consider it done, sir. -Good boy.

347
00:38:14,920 --> 00:38:18,420
你  叫什么名字?  你叫什么名字?
And you, whatever your name is... What is your name?

348
00:38:22,220 --> 00:38:28,320
-阿姆斯特丹  先生  -阿姆斯特丹  那我就叫纽约(注：纽约前名阿姆斯特丹)
-Amsterdam, sir. -Amsterdam. I'm New York.

349
00:38:28,720 --> 00:38:31,220
下次来别再一毛不拔了
Don't you never come in here empty-handed again.

350
00:38:31,420 --> 00:38:34,720
你得有所付出  讨讨我手下欢心
You gotta pay for the pleasure of my company.

351
00:38:35,020 --> 00:38:36,920
带上他一起行动  约翰
Take him for a boat ride, John.

352
00:38:37,120 --> 00:38:40,120
也许他能再救你一命
Who knows, but he might save your life again.

353
00:38:43,920 --> 00:38:46,620
被黎明小子抓到  会割断我们的喉咙
The Daybreak Boys catch us, they'll slit our throats.

354
00:38:46,920 --> 00:38:49,520
你要不闭嘴我就割断你的喉咙
I'll do it myself in a minute if you don't keep quiet.

355
00:38:49,720 --> 00:38:52,820
我不喜欢入夜后的港口
I never liked the harbor after dark.

356
00:38:53,020 --> 00:38:56,220
每天晚上都有士兵的尸体运来
And now each night they brung ashore the bodies of the soldiers.

357
00:38:56,620 --> 00:38:58,420
许多母亲甚至不知道儿子战死在何方
Many mothers have not even the solace...

358
00:38:58,720 --> 00:39:01,020
不知道儿子战死在何方
...of knowing where their sons have fallen.

359
00:39:01,320 --> 00:39:03,920
安提塔姆战役中我失去了长子
I lost my own eldest at Antietam.

360
00:39:04,120 --> 00:39:06,620
我和他母亲至今无法找回遗体
His mother and I were unable to recover his remains.

361
00:39:06,920 --> 00:39:09,520
那是幅悲惨的景象  战争不能永远持续下去
-It was a mournful sight. -The war can't last forever.

362
00:39:09,820 --> 00:39:12,420
可我们有自己的事要作
But we had business of our own.

363
00:39:21,220 --> 00:39:26,020
黎明小子已经来过了  洗劫一空  回去吧
The Daybreak Boys have been here, and there's nothing left. Let's go back.

364
00:39:29,820 --> 00:39:32,220
怎么回事
What the hell?

365
00:39:39,220 --> 00:39:41,220
吉米  趴下
Jimmy, get down!

366
00:39:43,620 --> 00:39:47,320
天啊  一定会把警察引来
Jesus, than bring the harbor cops for sure. Fuck off.

367
00:39:55,120 --> 00:39:57,220
去看看吧
Let's take a look.

368
00:40:00,020 --> 00:40:02,220
天啊  他们杀得鸡犬不留
Jesus, they killed everybody.

369
00:40:02,520 --> 00:40:05,220
除了一堆死螃蟹什么都没剩下
There's nothing here but a bunch of dead sea-crabs.

370
00:40:05,520 --> 00:40:07,720
快  走吧
Come on, let's go.

371
00:40:09,420 --> 00:40:11,720
-开船  -别走  等等阿姆斯特丹
-Shove off. - No, wait for Amsterdam.

372
00:40:12,020 --> 00:40:14,120
阿姆斯特丹在哪?
Where's Amsterdam?

373
00:40:16,620 --> 00:40:19,120
-笨蛋  截住他  -你在干什么?!
-No, you damn fool, take him! -What in the hell for?!

374
00:40:19,320 --> 00:40:21,420
看看我的货  不少于15美金
Look in my glims. I said no less than 15.

375
00:40:21,620 --> 00:40:24,920
-新鲜吗  -最多4小时
-Is this fresh? -Four hours most.

376
00:40:25,320 --> 00:40:27,820
非常感谢  先生们
Much obliged, gents.

377
00:40:34,920 --> 00:40:37,020
那是什么词?
What's that word?

378
00:40:38,020 --> 00:40:40,220
-意思是拿尸体  -不是问意思
-It means body snatchers. -I didn't ask the meaning.

379
00:40:40,520 --> 00:40:41,720
我问是个什么词
I asked the word.

380
00:40:42,520 --> 00:40:43,920
盗尸者
Ghoul.

381
00:40:45,520 --> 00:40:48,820
盗尸者?  好词
Ghoul? That's a good word.

382
00:40:49,120 --> 00:40:55,220
"盗尸帮杀人  五点区最新暴行"
"Ghoul Gang Slaughters. A fresh Outrage in the Five Points."

383
00:40:55,720 --> 00:40:58,020
-这标题你应该感到自豪  -多谢
-That's a notice you can be proud of. -Thank you.

384
00:40:58,320 --> 00:41:01,920
没出息  这么对待尸体
A low thing, to do that to a body. Low.

385
00:41:02,220 --> 00:41:04,420
为什么?  他们原本会空手而归
Why? They could have left that ship with nothing.

386
00:41:04,620 --> 00:41:08,720
可结果他们上了《警察宪报》 一份定期刊物
Instead they made The Police Gazette, a periodical of note.

387
00:41:09,020 --> 00:41:11,320
尸体应该埋在地下
A body's supposed to stay beneath the earth...

388
00:41:11,620 --> 00:41:14,620
384穿着木衣直到重生
...wearing a wooden coat until the Resurrection.

389
00:41:15,020 --> 00:41:17,820
这俩人和你一样都是爱尔兰人的后代
These two are a pair of sons of Irish bitches, same as you.

390
00:41:18,120 --> 00:41:20,020
别再搞他们了
It don't seem to bother them none.

391
00:41:20,320 --> 00:41:23,120
也许他们和你的是非观念不同吧
But then maybe they don't share your religious scruples.

392
00:41:23,320 --> 00:41:26,020
也许他们只是一对'费德兰奔'(Fidlam bens：黑话  什么都偷的贼)
Maybe they're just a couple of fidlam Bens.

393
00:41:31,720 --> 00:41:35,520
叫我什么的都有  可从没人叫我...
I've been called a lot of things, mister, but I ain't never been called...

394
00:41:35,920 --> 00:41:39,420
-费德兰奔  -费德兰奔  没氏
-Fidlam Bens. -Fidlam Bens. Right.

395
00:41:39,820 --> 00:41:45,920
如果我知道确切意思  我可能会反击
Well, if I knew what in the hell that meant, I'd be inclined to take offense.

396
00:41:46,220 --> 00:41:50,320
费德兰奔就是什么都偷的人  不论死活
A fidlam Bens is a fellow who steals anything, dead or alive...

397
00:41:50,720 --> 00:41:53,620
384太没出息以至无法建立任何形象
...because he's too low to work up a decent lay for himself.

398
00:41:54,020 --> 00:41:56,220
小心点  屠夫  小心点
Count that careful, Bill. Count that careful.

399
00:41:56,320 --> 00:41:59,220
-我告诉你他们就给了这么多  -小毛贼
-I'm telling you, that's all there is... -Now, chiseler...

400
00:41:59,620 --> 00:42:03,020
你说我们是小毛贼  这个词我明白  你知道吗?
If you'd said "chiseler," now there's a word I understand. You know?

401
00:42:03,320 --> 00:42:07,220
-你是这么叫我们吗?  -我能想出一大堆名词称呼你们
-Now, is that what you're calling us? -I can think of many things to call you.

402
00:42:07,620 --> 00:42:10,720
如果我问你是否称我们为'小毛贼'?
Right. But I asked if you was calling us chiselers.

403
00:42:11,120 --> 00:42:13,720
是又如何?
Supposing I am?

404
00:42:15,720 --> 00:42:18,320
那局面就不好收拾了
Well, then we got business.

405
00:42:19,320 --> 00:42:21,620
来吧
That we do.

406
00:42:28,520 --> 00:42:31,320
两块押麦格罗恩
-A fight! There's a fight! -Two bucks on McGloin.

407
00:42:31,620 --> 00:42:33,920
-四块押小伙子  -四块押小伙子
-Four bits on the kid. -Five bits on the kid.

408
00:42:34,220 --> 00:42:37,020
五块押阿姆斯特丹!
I got two on Amsterdam.

409
00:42:45,620 --> 00:42:48,920
上啊  麦格罗恩他不过是个小毛头
Come on, McGloin, he's just a kid.

410
00:42:49,520 --> 00:42:52,020
押回阿姆斯特丹四块
Four bits to back Amsterdam.

411
00:42:58,820 --> 00:43:01,620
小心他的左拳  麦格罗恩
Watch his left, McGloin. Watch his left.

412
00:43:41,220 --> 00:43:44,320
-行了  够了  够了  -你还有什么可说的?
-All right, l do. l do. -Anything to say now, huh?!

413
00:43:44,720 --> 00:43:47,220
行了  拉开他吧
OK, for chrissake. Drag him off.

414
00:43:47,420 --> 00:43:50,520
-够了  小子  你赢了  -行了  小子  你赢了  别犯傻了
-That's enough, kid. -You got him. Come on, kid, you won.

415
00:43:50,720 --> 00:43:53,520
麦格罗恩 他是个孩子
McGloin. He's a kid too, McGloin.

416
00:43:53,820 --> 00:43:56,320
你太老了  麦格罗恩
You're getting too old for it, McGloin.

417
00:44:18,020 --> 00:44:23,220
麦格罗恩  没鼻子耳朵的脑袋看起来是什么样的?
McGloin, how would that head look without the ears and the nose on it?

418
00:44:24,620 --> 00:44:26,920
这种脑袋你最好别碰  比尔
You'd better leave that head alone, Bill.

419
00:44:27,230 --> 00:44:30,630
我要把那脑袋的鼻子耳朵削掉
I think I'm gonna trim the ears and the beak off of that head.

420
00:44:32,030 --> 00:44:34,130
用这脑袋做碗好汤
Make a nice pot of soup of that head.

421
00:44:34,430 --> 00:44:37,030
有比这脑袋好味的脑袋  比尔
You could find a tastier head than that, Bill.

422
00:44:37,330 --> 00:44:40,630
没爱尔兰炖肉我根本没胃口
I ain't got the stomach for no Irish stew.

423
00:44:43,130 --> 00:44:48,130
大名鼎鼎的麦格罗恩差点成了个后生的手下败将
The mighty McGloin almost fishhooked by a sprat.

424
00:44:57,030 --> 00:45:01,030
第七天上帝休息  在休息前
On the seventh day, the Lord rested, but before that he did...

425
00:45:01,230 --> 00:45:06,930
他蹲在英格兰旁边 拉出来的东西  就是爱尔兰
...he squatted over the side of England, and what came out of him was Ireland.

426
00:45:07,330 --> 00:45:11,230
-没有冒犯你的意思  -没关系  先生  我是在这长大的
-No offense, son. -Oh, none taken, sir. I grew up here.

427
00:45:11,630 --> 00:45:15,930
关于爱尔兰的一切我都是在孤儿院听别人说的
All I ever knew of Ireland was in the talk of the others at the orphan asylum.

428
00:45:16,230 --> 00:45:21,030
你的祖先产在那个粪便岛的那个部位?
In which part of that excrementitious isle were your forebears spawned?

429
00:45:21,430 --> 00:45:26,830
我听说是克立  可从孤儿院起我就无法从口音证实这点了
I've been told Kerry, but I lost proof of it in my language at the asylum.

430
00:45:27,230 --> 00:45:30,330
我也在相似的环境中长大
I was raised in a very similar establishment myself.

431
00:45:30,630 --> 00:45:33,930
你看到属于我的东西都是某阶段的产物
Now everything you see belongs to me, to one degree or another.

432
00:45:34,230 --> 00:45:37,230
天堂广场的乞丐  报童和小贼
The beggars and newsboys and quick thieves here in Paradise.

433
00:45:37,530 --> 00:45:40,830
有钱的海员和低级酒吧  码头边劣质威士忌
The sailor dives and gin mills and blind tigers on the waterfront.

434
00:45:41,230 --> 00:45:44,130
盎格鲁人  双性人和中国人
The anglers and amusers, the she-hes and the Chinks.

435
00:45:44,330 --> 00:45:46,130
每个人都欠我钱  每个人都要付我钱
Everybody owes, everybody pays...

436
00:45:46,330 --> 00:45:52,030
384只有如此才能逆流而上  成长起来
...because that's how you stand up against the rising of the tide.

437
00:45:52,330 --> 00:45:55,530
-我说的对吗?  -没错  比尔
-Is that right, boys? -Yeah, Bill. That's right.

438
00:45:55,830 --> 00:45:57,930
加入我们的行列  为国效力
Enlist. Join up. Serve your country.

439
00:45:58,830 --> 00:46:01,530
响应征兵法的号召
Come on in out of the draft, boys.

440
00:46:01,730 --> 00:46:03,930
自告奋勇者可获50美元奖赏
Volunteer and get your $50 bonus.

441
00:46:05,930 --> 00:46:10,030
我们需要30000名自愿者  我们准备支付每位自愿者677美元
We need 30,000 volunteers, and we're prepared to pay $677 per volunteer.

442
00:46:10,430 --> 00:46:12,630
-请看看这个  -谢谢
-Please read this. Thank you. -Thanks.

443
00:46:12,930 --> 00:46:15,230
你要拿一张来填吗?
Would you like to take one of these to fill out?

444
00:46:15,530 --> 00:46:18,930
一日管三餐  一日管三餐
Three square meals a day. Three square meals a day.

445
00:46:19,230 --> 00:46:21,830
年轻人  应征入伍报效国家
Young man, enlist and serve your country.

446
00:46:22,130 --> 00:46:24,030
一日管三餐  先生
Three square meals a day, gentlemen.

447
00:46:24,230 --> 00:46:26,830
如果有兴趣  建议你看一下这个再决定是否应征
If you're interested, read this and consider joining.

448
00:46:27,230 --> 00:46:29,930
走到哪里人们都在谈论征兵
Everywhere you went people talked about the draft.

449
00:46:30,130 --> 00:46:33,230
支付300美元可免于应征
Now, you could buy your way out for $300...

450
00:46:33,530 --> 00:46:35,530
可谁有300美元呢?
...but who had $300?

451
00:46:35,730 --> 00:46:38,430
对我们来说和三百万也没区别
For us it might as well have been 3 million.

452
00:46:38,730 --> 00:46:42,530
对于征兵人员  他们害怕黑帮会找上我们
The recruiters? They was too scared of the gangs to come after us.

453
00:46:42,930 --> 00:46:47,530
而且  我们从没想过战争会打到纽约
Besides, we never dreamt the war would ever touch New York.

454
00:46:47,930 --> 00:46:49,230
早晨好  先生
Good morning, sir.

455
00:46:51,230 --> 00:46:52,630
你!
You!

456
00:46:53,230 --> 00:46:54,830
你可别撞上我
Don't you run into me.

457
00:46:56,230 --> 00:46:57,830
一报还一报
Fair enough.

458
00:47:02,830 --> 00:47:04,830
我说了别撞我的
I said, don't run into me!

459
00:47:05,130 --> 00:47:07,130
对不起
Well, sorry.

460
00:47:13,030 --> 00:47:16,230
-没丢东西吧?  -好象没有
-Everything in place? -It seems so.

461
00:47:16,630 --> 00:47:19,430
那我就留你继续享受上帝的恩惠和关怀
Well, then I leave you in the grace and favor of the Lord.

462
00:47:19,730 --> 00:47:21,830
-多谢  -好了
-Thank you. -That's right.

463
00:47:29,430 --> 00:47:32,630
这个死丫头
Oh, the dirty mab!

464
00:47:36,430 --> 00:47:38,030
不
Oh, no.

465
00:47:38,230 --> 00:47:40,630
-对不起-我来
-I'm sorry. -Allow me.

466
00:47:43,030 --> 00:47:46,330
-多谢你的好意  先生  -乐意效劳
-Thank you kindly, sir. -Oh, it's my pleasure.

467
00:47:47,230 --> 00:47:49,330
我希望你不会觉得我很冒昧
I hope you won't think me rude if I speak.

468
00:47:49,530 --> 00:47:51,730
否则我还是闭口为妙
I wouldn't want to appear forward.

469
00:47:51,930 --> 00:47:56,530
先生  那要看你说什么
Well, sir, that depends on what you say.

470
00:48:04,830 --> 00:48:09,030
如果我夸你是纽约最漂亮的女孩你会认为我很鲁莽吗?
Would you call me reckless if I said you were the prettiest girl in New York?

471
00:48:09,330 --> 00:48:11,930
只是在纽约吗?
Only New York?

472
00:48:13,830 --> 00:48:15,030
我到站了
This is my stop.

473
00:48:17,330 --> 00:48:20,130
我可以陪你走一会儿吗?
May I walk with you a little then?

474
00:48:20,430 --> 00:48:23,030
先生  这样太鲁莽了
That, sir, would be too bold.

